50
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,440
So to show that difference, we can say,

51
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:44,400
Tokyo Tower is not as high as Tokyo Sky
Tree.

52
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,840
That makes it totally clear they aren't
equal.

53
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,920
The formula is almost the same.

54
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:52,600
We just add one little word, not, right
before the first as.

55
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:55,900
This structure always means that the first
thing, item A,

56
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:59,600
is less than item B in that quality we're
talking about.

57
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:04,360
So, Tokyo Tower is less high than Tokyo
Sky Tree. Makes sense, right?

58
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:07,020
And hey, here's a little bonus tip for ya.

59
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,480
In these negative sentences,

60
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:11,800
you can also swap out the first as for the
word so.

61
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:16,200
You could say, Tokyo Tower is not so high
as Tokyo Sky Tree.

62
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:19,360
It means the exact same thing. Pretty
cool.

